body:
### Description

I've noticed a glitch with jdtls and nvim-lspconfig, using lazy nvim. When I create a new file, the warnings and errors don't show up as expected. However, when I open an older file, the warnings and errors start working again, even if I'm editing and saving that older file. Also, when I perform code actions, it seems to execute them for an older file, even if it's not currently open. When deleting that file it sticks onto the next file I choose to open, repeating the process for any new files . This appears to happens with only jdtls, pyright having no problems.

[Edit]
After more testing, it does not work for new java files. I created two java files and for the first one it works as intended. But still, for the last one it still doesn't work.

This is the info from LSP:
Language client log: /home/matei/.local/state/nvim/lsp.log
